<x-color><param>white</param>**</x-color>* gorg.data.nodes
<x-color><param>white</param>***</x-color>* [[file:data/nodes.py::class%20Node:][gorg.data.nodes.Node]]

<x-color><param>white</param>****</x-color>* methods
<x-color><param>white</param>*****</x-color>* __init__
- constructor function

- initialized with an index number and an optional property dictionary 

<x-color><param>white</param>*****</x-color>* getindex

- used for getting the index number of the node

<x-color><param>white</param>*****</x-color>* getprops

- used for getting the complete dictionary of node properties

<x-color><param>white</param>*****</x-color>* getprop

- used for querying the value of a specific property

<x-color><param>white</param>*****</x-color>* setprop

- used for overwriting a new key and value to the node properties

<x-color><param>white</param>****</x-color>* usage

- Nodes are the atomic storage unit of gorg data.

- Each node is a member of a Network, and has a unique index number within that network.
- Apart from the unique index number, nodes are basically just dictionaries of properties.


<x-color><param>white</param>***</x-color>* [[file:data/nodes.py::class%20Network:][gorg.data.nodes.Network]]

